<p>19 May 1918<br/>Whit Sunday<br/>Nothing of much importance to note Australians reported to have taken a Village near Albert and 360 prisoners Very warm weather Went to Service in Y.M. in the evening.</p>
<p>1918 May 20<br/>Whitsun Monday<br/>Bank Holiday<br/>This appears to be something different to what the English people usually have on Whit Monday. Usually there is a holiday but all appear to be working today. Same old Camp routine. Very warm. Air Raid on London last night.</p>
